# Lab 3 - Linux File Permissions

## Objective

Learn Linux file permissions using symbolic and numeric methods.

## Commands Used

```bash
mkdir PermissionLab
cd PermissionLab

touch notes.txt
touch script.sh
touch secret.txt

ls -l

chmod +x script.sh
chmod -w notes.txt
chmod 777 secret.txt
chmod 755 script.sh
chmod 644 notes.txt
chmod 600 secret.txt

ls -l
stat notes.txt
```

## Skills Practiced

- Viewing permissions
- Changing permissions
- Numeric permissions
- Symbolic permissions
- Viewing file metadata

---

## Key Learning

Linux permissions are essential for protecting files and controlling access to system resources.
- Deleting files
- Searching files
# Lab 4 – Linux Users and Groups

## Objective

Learn how Linux manages user accounts, groups, and user-related system files.

## Commands Used

```bash
whoami
who
id
groups
cat /etc/passwd
cat /etc/group
echo $USER
echo $HOME
echo $SHELL
```

## Skills Practiced

- Identifying the current user
- Viewing logged-in users
- Checking UID and GID
- Viewing group memberships
- Reading user account information
- Reading group information
- Viewing environment variables

## Result

Successfully explored Linux user management and understood how user and group information is stored on the system.
